  "detailedRequirements": "<p><span style=\"font-size:13px\">Yo! &nbsp;Salesforce gurus of the crowd. &nbsp;We need help sending emails to more than one recipient. &nbsp;More people to see our awesome Salesforce Ideas. &nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p><span>Our custom setting and related Apex code that allows us to send emails when a new idea is posted in our Salesforce.com org, needs updated.</span></p>\n\n<h2>Technical Overview for this Challenge</h2>\n\n<p>We have logic in place that sends emails when Salesforce Ideas are posted. &nbsp;We need the custom setting Email_Notifications__c.object.Recipient_on_Emails_to_All__c to be updated from Email field type to a string field type. &nbsp;The cooresponding Apex code in the Utilty.cls needs changed to allow for comma delimited list. &nbsp;This &quot;list&quot; will be stored in the custom setting. &nbsp;Example: x@test.com, xy@test.com. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>We have also attached our Ideas triggers and classes. &nbsp;This will allow you to test Ideas and email notifications.</p>\n\n<h2>Steps to Get Source Code</h2>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>A zip file of source code will be available in forums.</li>\n\t<li>Load into your dev org.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Details of the challenge</h2>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Update custom setting&nbsp;<span>Email_Notifications__c.object.Recipient_on_Emails_to_All__c to string field type instead of email type.</span></li>\n\t<li>Update all code in Apex to allow for the updated custom setting.</li>\n\t<li>Assume the custom setting value is one email address if no comma is present, otherwise parse the comma delimited list (multiple email addresses).</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Acceptance Criteria</h2>\n\n<p>After the changes, the application should allow storing of mulitple email addresses in the custom setting (comma delimited). &nbsp;The code should function the same way sending out an email whenever a new idea is posted, but now it should send to multiple email addresses.</p>\n",
